children.subject:
Google form?

Might have to sift through some not so great feedback to get to any valuable feedback, but you'd have to do that anyway even in a spreadsheet

Also, if you have feedback on what we can do better or how we can improve the effectiveness of office hours, please let us know. I believe most of us are new to online-based instruction and are still learning the logistics of it along with you. (There is a column for feedback on the spreadsheet though I'm not sure that's the most effective way for collecting that feedback?)

Thanks TAs and prof for being super active. Just few comments: This is my last course. Usually I have seen office hours questions being posted in Piazza and studenrs/TAs will update when that question was answered in the video. I have seen this to be very effective to view only interesting questions. Also I am not able to view questions asked in prior office hours when I go to slido with respective event IDs. may be I am facing some issue? or is everyone facing this?
Are there no office hours tonight due to the holiday?

history.content:
The following will be the regular office hour schedule every week.
  • Monday: Jeremy 9:00 p.m. - 10:00 p.m.
  • Tuesday: Tiancheng 9:00 p.m. - 10:00 p.m.
  • Thursday: Murali 7:00 p.m. - 8:00 p.m.
  • Saturday: Michael 2:00 p.m. - 3:00 p.m.
You can check the schedule, event code and link on this spreadsheet. We will also be posting the main topics/questions discussed during the respective office hours on the spreadsheet. This should help you find the relevant office hours quickly. Thank you!
